<li id="cite_note-nprMusicalBookofMormon-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-nprMusicalBookofMormon_51-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2011" class="citation web cs1">Smith, Robert (March 24, 2011). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.npr.org/2011/03/24/134803453/on-broadway-a-mormon-swipe-at-everything">"On Broadway, A 'Mormon' Swipe At ... Everything"</a>. National Public Radio<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">March 24,</span> 2011</span>. <q>There's a line where they say, 'I believe that God lives on a planet named Kolob,'" Baker says. "That is an actual Mormon belief. We do believe that. But taken out of context—or in context—you do not want anyone to know you actually believe it.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=On+Broadway%2C+A+%27Mormon%27+Swipe+At+...+Everything&amp;rft.pub=National+Public+Radio&amp;rft.date=2011-03-24&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2011%2F03%2F24%2F134803453%2Fon-broadway-a-mormon-swipe-at-everything&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKolob" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
